<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<Data CreatedBy="admin" CreatedOn="634127350059897387" UpdatedBy="admin" UpdatedOn="634134210640696415">
  <Properties />
  <Nodes>
    <Header Code="HeaderElement1" Type="Subtitle" ShowInTOC="0"><![CDATA[The example]]></Header>
    <Paragraph Code="ParagraphElement1"><![CDATA[<p>The demonstrated <em>ListBox </em>contains defined <em>DataSource </em>as the array of objects that have public properties such as 'ID', 'FullName' and 'Photo' with ResourceHandle type.  And the 'Photo' property is set as value of the <em>ListBox</em>  <em>ImageMember </em>property, 'ID' property is set as value of the <em>ListBox  ValueMember</em> property and 'FullName' property is set as value of the <em>ListBox  DisplayMember</em>  property.  After the app is loaded, <em>ListBox </em>contains user image area for each.</p>]]></Paragraph>
    <Header Code="HeaderElement2" Type="Subtitle" ShowInTOC="0"><![CDATA[General Info]]></Header>
    <Paragraph Code="ParagraphElement2"><![CDATA[<p>The Visual WebGui <em>ListBox </em>contains the following properties for working with data:<br /><em>DataSource </em>&ndash; defines the data source that the connector binds to;<br /><em>ColorMember </em>&ndash; defines the color member of the data sources;<br /><em>DisplayMember </em>- specifies the name of an object property that is contained in the collection specified by <em>DataSource </em>property. The property is displayed as text of the item. The default is an empty string (&quot;&quot;);<br /><em>ValueMember </em>&ndash; defines value of the ListBox item. Represents the name of an object property that is contained in the collection specified by the DataSource property. The default is an empty string (&quot;&quot;);<br /><em>ImageMember </em>- defines image for the ListBox item. Represents the name of an object property that is contained in the collection specified by the DataSource property. The default is an empty string (&quot;&quot;).<br /> And the following events:<br /><em>DataSourceChanged </em>&ndash; occurs when value of the <em>DataSource </em>property is changed. <br /><em>DisplayMemberChanged </em>&ndash; occurs when value of the <em>DisplayMember </em>property is changed.<br /><em>ValueMemberChanged </em>- occurs when value of the <em>ValueMember </em>property is changed.<br />&nbsp;</p>]]></Paragraph>
  </Nodes>
</Data>
